Title: Pectoral, Jackal Shaped Anubis
Medium: Egyptian faience with blue-green and black glaze
Description: The black painted designs on this faience pectoral have faded. On the front the jackal of Anubis lies on a shrine, on the back side a "djed" pillar is flanked by "tyet" knots.
Provenance: Dikran Kelekian, New York and Paris [date and mode of acquisition unknown]; Henry Walters, Baltimore, by purchase; Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.
Creator: Egyptian
